    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-05-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1263"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1263">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 313.115/3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Hamm</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 103.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-05-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 12, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received a communication,
                    dated May 5, 1913, from Mr. Frank L. Peckham, attorney at law, of Washington,
                        <pb facs="0875" n="759" xml:id="pg_759"/> D. C, saying that the San Luis
                    Mining Company, one of the properties owned by Mrs. Phoebe A. Hearst, having
                    headquarters at Socavon, District of San Dimas, Durango, Mexico, has been forced
                    to contribute the sum of $2,500, Mexican, to the so-called Constitutionalists in
                    that district.</p>
                <p>You are instructed to protest unofficially against the action of the so-called
                    Constitutionalists to the Constitutionalist authorities.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
